abstract: Readers discuss whether enough Republicans will defy their leadership and vote to hear from John Bolton. Also: The New York Civil Liberties Union, on bail reform.

abstract: Tyrone Abraham served his time. His story shows what happens when a state’s criminal justice system collides with federal immigration enforcement.
snippet: Tyrone Abraham served his time. His story shows what happens when a state’s criminal justice system collides with federal immigration enforcement.
lead_paragraph: Editors’ Note: On Jan. 29, Gov. Andrew Cuomo unconditionally pardoned Mr. Abraham, and the United States Court of Appeals for the Second Circuit granted him an emergency stay of removal.

abstract: Just kidding. The creator of the acclaimed sitcom, Michael Schur, discusses political parallels, silly tortures and what the show had to say about “the impossibility of being alive.”
snippet: Just kidding. The creator of the acclaimed sitcom, Michael Schur, discusses political parallels, silly tortures and what the show had to say about “the impossibility of being alive.”
lead_paragraph: Michael Schur swears he didn’t name Michael, the avuncular architect played by Ted Danson on Schur’s metaphysical sitcom, “The Good Place,” after himself. The character was actually based on St. Michael the Archangel, who according to Christian tradition is involved in the final judgment of souls.

abstract: As Mr. Biden campaigned in the state, residents appeared unmoved: “I don’t think much about anything Joni Ernst says.”
snippet: As Mr. Biden campaigned in the state, residents appeared unmoved: “I don’t think much about anything Joni Ernst says.”
lead_paragraph: MUSCATINE, Iowa — Senator Joni Ernst of Iowa, a Republican, wondered aloud about her Democratic constituents as they wrestled with a final decision before the looming Iowa caucuses, particularly those considering supporting former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr.

abstract: The plan would discard the longtime goal of granting the Palestinians a full-fledged state. President Trump called it “a win-win” for both sides; Palestinian leaders immediately rejected it.
snippet: The plan would discard the longtime goal of granting the Palestinians a full-fledged state. President Trump called it “a win-win” for both sides; Palestinian leaders immediately rejected it.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump on Tuesday unveiled his long-awaited Middle East peace plan with a flourish, releasing a proposal that would give Israel most of what it has sought over decades of conflict while offering the Palestinians the possibility of a state with limited sovereignty.

headline_main: Watch Live: Trump’s Legal Team Wraps Up Defense

abstract: The president’s lawyer spoke about the damage wrought by partisanship in a final appeal to the closely divided Senate to acquit Mr. Trump.
snippet: The president’s lawyer spoke about the damage wrought by partisanship in a final appeal to the closely divided Senate to acquit Mr. Trump.
lead_paragraph: “This should end now, as quickly as possible,” Pat Cipollone, one of President Trump’s lawyers, said  just before 3 p.m. on Tuesday, bringing an abrupt close to the defense team’s arguments not to remove Mr. Trump from office.
